rmation. [CLS] [SEP] Their contextual semantic similarity model is different from our language modeling approach to measuring context similarity. [CLS] [SEP] It also made use of part-of-speech tag information, whereas our method is simpler and does not require part-of- speech tagging. [CLS] [SEP] They combined the two sources of information by weighting the two individual scores, whereas we made use of the average rank for combination. [CLS] [SEP] In this paper, we proposed a new method to mine new word translations from comparable corpora, by combining context and transliteration information, which are complementary sources of information. [CLS] [SEP] We evaluated our approach on six months of Chinese and English Gigaword corpora, with encouraging results. [CLS] [SEP] We thank Jia Li for implementing the EM algorithm to train transliteration probabilities. [CLS] [SEP] This research is partially supported by a research grant R252000-125112 from National University of Singapore Academic Research Fund.